cs.LG, cs.CV, cs.CR, cs.AI, cs.DS 

This paper deals with machine learning and optimization techniques to learn flexible representations that minimize the capability of an adversarial critic. The paper also demonstrates the approach on two problems: making decisions free from discrimination and removing private information from images. Therefore, the most likely sub-categories are cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition), and cs.CR (Cryptography and Security). Additionally, the paper also involves optimization techniques, which makes cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) a likely sub-category. Finally, the paper involves data privacy, which makes cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) a possible sub-category.
